# Windsurf Python Rules

## Import Rules

- ALWAYS: `from json import loads` NOT `import json`
- ALWAYS: `from asyncio import run` NOT `import asyncio`
- ALWAYS: `from os import environ` NOT `import os`
- ALL imports at top of file — NO inline imports
- Import order: stdlib → third-party → local

## Type Rules

- NO `Any` type — use `object` if unconstrained
- NO `Optional[X]` — use `X | None`
- Annotations on EVERYTHING: `x: int = 1`, `def f(x: str) -> int:`
- `ClassVar[int]` for class constants

## Class Rules

- `__slots__` on ALL classes
- `dataclass(slots=True)` for data containers
- `match/case` over `if/elif` for 3+ branches

## Style Rules

- Shebang + path comment on every file: `#!/usr/bin/env python3` / `# file.py — desc.`
- `from __future__ import annotations` at top
- 88 char max line length
- `is None` / `is not None` — never `== None`
- `if flag:` — never `== True`
- No mutable defaults: `def f(x=[])` → `def f(x: list[str] | None = None):`

## Security Rules

- NEVER `eval` / `exec` / `shell=True`
- NEVER `pickle.loads` on untrusted data
- Use `secrets` for tokens, `hashlib.sha256+` for hashing
- Parameterised SQL only

## Testing

- `pytest` + `pytest-asyncio`
- Test boundary inputs: empty, None, wrong type

## Key Files

- `skills/python-pro/SKILL.md` — full rule set
- `ruff.toml` — linter config
- `mypy.ini` — type checking config
- `cli/` — core package
